cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically word sense disambiguation using neural models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes methods for reducing the size of neural models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of pre-trained BERT word vectors also suggests the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed methods, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of semantic relationships between senses in WordNet suggests the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
